				<p>This project was built as a Java Dynamic Web Project using Eclipse. Basic logic is performed in a JSP Servlet file, and communicates with an Oracle SQL database with a DAO jdbc class.</p>
                <p>This project uses JavaScript to display the form for the user and set date constraints in the user's form. The form will also change dynamically depending on the number of passengers a user wants to add to a ticket.</p>
                <p>Once the ticket has been generated as a method of the Ticket Java class, it will be displayed on the web app for the user, and will also be saved to the downloads folder by using a Buffered File Writer.</p>
